Post title: Add course_completion to SQL query?
Post description: Hi all, I have the following sql already running for a message, and am wanting to shoe-horn in something to grab "timecompleted" from the course_completions table, but sql joins etc. aren't a strong point.  I have elsewhere code for getting the completion status, but that involves getting new course objects etc., and as this message is potentially being generated for hundreds of users I want to keep it as lean as possible. So here's the main bit of the message, with the associated SQL to grab the user's current courses and the expiry dates; desired is to grab the associated timecompleted so a quick check on whether it's NULL will determine whether "(completed)" is printed beside the course or not. 
```text
$rs = $DB->get_recordset_select('user', "id $in", $params);

foreach ($rs as $user) {
    $msg = 'Hello ' . $user->firstname . ' ' . $user->lastname . '.<br/><br/>';
    $msg .= 'You are currently enrolled in the following courses:<br/><br/>';

    $timenow = round(time(), -2);
    $sql = "SELECT c.id, c.fullname, ue.timeend
        FROM {course} c
        JOIN {enrol} e ON e.courseid = c.id
        JOIN {user_enrolments} ue ON ue.enrolid = e.id
        WHERE ue.userid =  $user->id AND ue.status = 'ENROL_USER_ACTIVE' AND e.status = 'ENROL_INSTANCE_ENABLED'
        AND ue.timestart < $timenow AND (ue.timeend = 0 OR ue.timeend > $timenow)";
    $results = $DB->get_records_sql($sql, $params);

    $msg .= '<ul>';
    foreach($results as $result){
        $msg .= '<li>' . $result->fullname . '<br/>';
        $dateEnd = $result->timeend;
        if($dateEnd != 0){
            $dateEndPrev = strtotime('-1 day',$dateEnd);    
            $msg .= 'Expires end of day ' . date('d/m/Y',$dateEndPrev);
        }
        $msg .= '</li>';
    }
    $msg .= '</ul><br/>';

    $msg .= "You can access your courses by logging in at blah blah...";

    $sub='Notification - new course enrolment';
    if(!email_to_user($user,$aduser,$sub,$msg,$msg)){
        $emailerrors .= '<br/>Email error, could not email ' . $user->firstname . ' ' . $user->lastname . ', username ' .$user->username;
    }
}
$rs->close();
```
 Any pointers greatly appreciated.  Or would there actually be no benefit over using the course_object / completion_info / is_course_complete method?
