Post title: Database
Post description: Hello guys, what code can use to get and access the records by using my sql _functions ?. thank you.
Comments associated with the post: 
Comment 1: One of the common problem in older PHP code using the `mysql_` functions to access the database directly. Try to use this code : 
```text
function get_user_id( $name )
{
  $db = mysql_connect( 'localhost', 'root', 'password' );
  mysql_select_db( 'users' );

  $res = mysql_query( "SELECT id FROM users WHERE login='".$name."'" );
  while( $row = mysql_fetch_array( $res ) ) { $id = $row[0]; }

  return $id;
}

var_dump( get_user_id( 'jack' ) );
```
 Notice that the use of the `mysql_connect` function to access the database. Also notice the query in which we use string concatenation to add the `$name` parameter to the query.
Comment 2: Data can be fetched from MySQL tables by executing SQL SELECT statement through PHP function mysql_query. You have several options to fetch data from MySQL. The most frequently used option is to use function mysql_fetch_array() . This function returns row as an associative array, a numeric array, or both. This function returns FALSE if there are no more rows.
Comment 3: First, this is the forum for Moodle's database activity, not for developer questions. Second, Moodle supports multiple databases, not just MySQL. So, you need to use Moodle database abstraction layer https://docs.moodle.org/dev/Data_manipulation_API
